-- PGE May Buy Out Polish State-Owned Stakes in Units This Year, PAP Reports
-- B y   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 2010-12-28T11:22:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/pge-may-buy-out-polish-state-owned-stakes-in-units-this-year-pap-reports.html
PGE SA, Poland’s biggest power
utility, may buy out state-owned stakes in mining, trading and
distribution units by the end of this year, the PAP newswire
reported, without saying where it got the information, and
citing analysts it didn’t name as giving a book value for the
stakes of about 4.1 billion zloty.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nathaniel Espino at 
 nespino@bloomberg.net  